title: Student left fighting for life after TAMPON caused TSS
text: Student, 19, who put her severe headache down to 'exam stress' is left fighting for life after a TAMPON gave her a deadly infection Phoebee Bambury, 19, spent two weeks in hospital after contracting TSS The student initially thought her severe headache was caused by exam stress She eventually realised her symptoms matched those of toxic shock syndrome In hospital body continued to react to the infection, causing days of vomiting, fevers and her body to swell so much, she put on 5kg because of the fluid
